<br>
I was running out of money, so I decided to sell a velium diamond ring to raise some money to finish off.  I got a tell asking if I would trade the ring for the Platinum Dragon Totem.  I asked my guild and nobody seemed to know much about it, so, being the posessor of about 100 ulthork tusks, and liking my chances of getting another diamond and knowing a 250 skill jewler, I pulled the trigger on the deal.<br>
<br>
I have a silvery mask which allows me to cast identify on stuff and it identifies as &quot;Idol of Veeshan&quot;...this is quite perplexing to me.  I can't seem to find any info on this item anywhere, and was wondering if any of you folks know.  It is a handheld 30hp 50mana that goes in either hand. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaeronwyaoife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeronwy Aoife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 2:26:21 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Platinum Dragon Totem? (new druid seeks help)</span><hr size=1> Hello!!<br>
<br>
My druid is now level 44, but she got one of these in her early 20s I believe... I used it in my main hand, with a Testament of Vanear in the off hand for a very long time while learning how to kite... I simply kept my weapon handy in a main inventory slot to swap out if I needed it quickly, such as at the end of a kite when I didn't want to use the mana to nuke...<br>
<br>
Extra mana and hit points are a very nice thing to have at the lower levels, and, I suspect, at higher levels when wis is maxed... it's very light so I will likely begin to carry it around again just to see how useful it may be in the future... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uericfate.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EricFate</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 4:49:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> All things considered.</span><hr size=1> Nice move.<br>
<br>
The totem is pretty darn useful to have around, especially with an &quot;up and coming&quot; character. It isn't terribly much in demand...because as you discovered first hand, it can be so frightfully rare that people just forget it exists. It's not a best of class item, but it does make up for a number of shortcomings your Druid will face from 1st to 30th. After that, I'd suggest either banking it to use with other new characters later on, or handing it around in the guild. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubobnoblongwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobnob Longwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 5:09:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Platinum Dragon Totem? (new druid seeks help)</span><hr size=1> okay, but if I sell it, about how much is it worth?<br>
<br>
and what mob does it drop off of, I just don't know. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubobnoblongwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bobnob Longwalker</A> at: 5/21/01 5:25:28 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useolblade777.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seolblade777</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/01 6:04:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Platinum Dragon Totem? (new druid seeks help)</span><hr size=1> Hrm, if I am thinking of the right item you are talking about, i believe it is worth 100-400 plat average <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubixenedar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BixenEdar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/22/01 5:35:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Platinum Dragon Totem? (new druid seeks help)</span><hr size=1> Drops in sol a, rare off of the high shaman. <p><BR>Bixen 60 druid
<BR>Lords of Edelo Innoruuk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/22/01 8:33:25 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Platinum Dragon Totem? (new druid seeks help)</span><hr size=1> The problem is that the item is so rare it doesn't really have a value.  But think about it this way ... 50 mana would equate to 5wis at level 50 or 10wis at level 25.  (And +mana is, in a way, better than +wis because it isn't affected by the 200 wis cap.)  Any handheld item that had that kind of wis would be worth a good amount.  Add in the 30hp (nothing to sneeze at even at 50+, but amazing for a lower level druid), and you've got a really nice item.  Definitely more than 100-400pp, I would think.  As long as you have an ok weapon to switch it out with when you need to raise your melee skills or just melee to finish off a mob ... I can't think of many things that would be better in your primary hand up till you got a Paw (or maybe cone of the mystics, but even that would be a tossup).<br>
<br>
When you consider switching it out, remember that 50 mana equates to a LOT of wis ... so the totem would be much better to have than, say, a 3wis weapon.  My advice would be to carry the totem most of the time and carry around a blackjack or something (blackjacks are 7/21 magic and go for ridiculously cheap on my server, a couple hundred plat) for melee purposes. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>55th Preserver, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3233.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.showMessage?topicID=3212.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.emailToFriend?topicID=3230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.threadControl?topicID=3230.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3230.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovedruidicequipment.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3230.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgrovespells">Spells<option value="thedruidsgrovequests">Quests<option value="thedruidsgrovedruidicequipment">Druidic Equipment<option value="thedruidsgrovehuntingguide">Hunting Guide<